page_content: The page reports on a paragliding accident in St. Moritz, resulting in fatal injuries.
The page discusses changes in the taxation of imputed rental value for federal tax in the canton of Graubünden for the years 1999-2000.
The page discusses the proposal for the installation of a heart defibrillator in the building of the Cantonal Parliament of Graubünden.
The page discusses various governmental decisions, including zoning plans, health promotion, and unfair competition laws.
The page discusses the Gebäudeenergieausweis der Kantone (GEAK) and GEAK Plus, tools for assessing building energy efficiency and modernization.
The page provides information on the procedure for COVID-19 testing, including registration and what to expect at the test station.
The page provides information on traffic restrictions due to the Engadin Skimarathon, including road closures and parking guidelines.
